xxl.core.cursors.wrappers

Class EnumerationCursor<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.cursors.AbstractCursor<E>
      • xxl.core.cursors.wrappers.EnumerationCursor<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements returned by this iteration.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<E>, Cursor<E>

    public class EnumerationCursor<E>
extends AbstractCursor<E>
    This class provides a wrapper for enumerations, i.e., an emumeration can be accessed via the cursor interface. The constructor of this class takes an enumeration and wraps it to a cursor. The cursor functionality is projected on the enumeration, therefore the methods remove, update and reset are not supported.
    See Also:
    Iterator, Cursor, AbstractCursor, Enumeration

      • nextObject

        protected E nextObject()
        Returns the next element in the iteration. This element will be accessible by some of the enumeration-cursor's methods, e.g., update or remove, until a call to next or peek occurs. This is calling next or peek proceeds the iteration and therefore its previous element will not be accessible any more.
        Specified by:
        nextObject in class AbstractCursor<E>
        Returns:
        the next element in the iteration.
